Ho,ho,hoe! 🤣⛄️🎅🏿

I absolutely love the holidays! I am Bonquisha the Elf! I send out Christmas cards, I put up my pink Christmas tree, I listen to Christmas music nonstop. "Now Behold The Lamb" is top-tier Christmas music. It's advent season and as a #churchgirl, I'm all about celebrating the birth of Christ. Jesus is my homeboy and I'mma drink and be merry for Him. I'm really starting to understand how precious I am in God's sight and it has been a game changer.

I know this season can be tough for a lot of people but know that God is a comforter. I've been diving deep into the book of Psalms and I've been mediating on this scripture: 
“But you, Lord, are a shield around me, my glory, the One who lifts my head high.”
Psalms 3:3 NIV

Whatever you're going through, know that God can bring you through it and lift your head. Our crowns fall when looking down, so look up unto God. 

Oh, and latte stencils have me thinking I'm a barista. Super fun & an inexpensive Amazon find. #christmas #christmastree #jesuschrist #adventseason #coffeetime #coffeeaddict #holidaze #grinchmas #loveislove #jesusisthereasonfortheseason

My 2023 motto: "I ain't wastin' time that I'm never gettin' back
Takin' less L's, makin' more M's"

Two of my prayers for 2023 is to travel more & have more fun. As I walk in my purpose, I want to be sure that I am enjoying the pleasures that God has blessed us with. God doesn't want us to be anxious about anything and He wants us to enjoy life. Last week, I spent a couple of days in Nassau, Bahamas just chilling. Ms. Booked & Busy chilled hard af in Nassau. 

I stayed at Breezes- it's an all-inclusive resort that was perfect for the chill vibes that my soul needed. I had a beach front room that included a butler. Sis didn't need to go anywhere. Conch fritters were delivered to me as I got some writing done on my patio. Pina Coladas were constantly refilled. I swam in the ocean, rested in the hot tub, met new friends, & had dope conversations. I wanted to start the new year well rested before the grind continued. 

And it's already started! I'm typing this as I'm flying to Utah for Sundance! I was the wardrobe supervisor for this chilling thriller called birth/rebirth staring my gurls @itisijudyreyes1 & @ajandsg2 and it's premiering at Sundance. I'm about to be a chocolate snow bunny on the slopes. 

This is God answering my prayers of travel and fun already! 

Cheers to a weekend of networking, looking fly & warm & being Black af at Sundance. 

Sidebar: Pilates does a body good. I was giving in my @skims swim suit. #skimsswim #skims #breezesbahamas #bahamas #chillvibes #vacationvibes #vacay #nassaubahamas #grindmode #sundance2023 #sundancefilmfestival #blackatsundance #birthrebirth

This adorable homemade Heart Shaped Pizza is so simple. 

Ingredients
▢ 1 ball pizza dough homemade or store-bought
▢ 2 tbsp. olive oil, divided
▢ 30 pepperoni
▢ 1/4 c. pizza sauce
▢ 1 1/2 c. shredded mozzarella
▢ 3 tbsp. grated parmesan cheese
▢ 2 tsp. chopped parsley or basil 
Instructions
 
Preheat oven to 450°Fs. Line a pizza pan with parchment paper, set aside.
Fold each pepperoni in half and cut it into heart shapes using kitchen shears. Place on a paper towel-lined plate and microwave for 15 seconds on high. Dab any excess grease off, set aside.
Lightly flour a surface and roll the dough into a heart shape, about 16 inches tall. Fold edges over and press to create the crust. 
Transfer the pizza dough to a prepared baking sheet. Brush with olive oil, then dock the crust with a fork to prevent bubbles from forming.
Place in the oven and bake for 6 minutes. Remove and spread sauce over top, then add cheese and pepperoni. 
Return to the oven and bake for 8-12 minutes or until the crust is golden brown and the pepperoni is crispy. Remove from the oven and top with fresh parsley or basil, if desired. Let stand for 5 minutes before cutting.

It's Champagne Mami's Birthday! Gosh, I have so much to say, I really need to do a Fly Girl Rants! Soon! I miss it! As I embark on another year, I just thank God. I wouldn't be Fly Carla without God's grace. I am who I am because of the great I am. I thank God for my health, mentally & physically. I thank God for my family. I thank God for His protection. I thank God for clarity. I thank God for removing people & things that do not serve me. I give God all the praise. He opens doors for me that no man can shut. He gives me ideas & creativity. I have no idea how people navigate this crazy world without a relationship with God. I have angels always around me, they are on guard day & night. I am a grateful fly girl. 

And because I love to talk sh!t - in my problematic queen's voice: "My winnin' streak still hasn't peaked, you little dust ball." - Nicki Minaj 

Cheers to more life! 🎊🎉🥂♉️💕🫶🏾🍾🙌🏾🙏🏾
